Description: Generates physically based sky environment maps and radiance samples using the
    spectral Hosek–Wilkie and Prague atmosphere models. Functions write
    high-dynamic-range OpenEXR domes in latitude–longitude
    projections, compute per-direction RGB or 55-channel values, and optionally
    composite location-accurate star fields. Features include automatic sun and moon positioning from date,
    time and location, support for sea-level and high-altitude observers, wide-
    spectrum coefficients, and multithreaded C++/Rcpp acceleration for fast,
    high-resolution output.
